d# dmenu - Custom Centered & Fuzzy Build

An elegant, patched, and optimized X11 dynamic menu configured meticulously to blend into the `everforest_dark_hard` environment. 
This personal configuration strips away the classic utility top bar layout, introducing a floating centered interface built for maximum keyboard efficiency.

---

Ensure you have the core X11, freetype2, and Xft development headers installed via your system package manager (e.g., pacman -S base-devel libx11 libxft libxinerama).

---

## ✨ Features & Applied Patches

- **Centered Layout (`center`):** Spawns `dmenu` dead center on your active monitor. It includes a custom height, width, and explicit item layout constraints so it reads more like a modern desktop command palette.
- **Fuzzy Matching (`fuzzymatch`):** Upgrades standard character-by-character prefix filtering to intuitive, non-consecutive string fuzzy matching. 
- **Safe 3-Column Theme Matrix:** Custom configuration block rewritten to consistently hold `[Color Value, Background Value, Accent/Border Value]` mapping structure safely preventing X11 color allocation segmentation faults.

---

## 🎨 The Everforest Color Blueprint

The color indices (`config.def.h`) match the exact Alacritty-tested Everforest values. Text foreground colors dynamically shift when active to provide superior contrast levels against the green accent bars:

```c
static const char *colors[SchemeLast][3] = {
	/* fg         bg         border/alt */
	[SchemeNorm]          = { "#d3c6aa", "#272e33", "#272e33" }, // Muted cream text on deep grey
	[SchemeSel]           = { "#2d353b", "#a7c080", "#a7c080" }, // Dark charcoal text on soft green highlight
	[SchemeSelHighlight]  = { "#47523a", "#a7c080", "#a7c080" }, // Deep forest-green for matches inside selection
	[SchemeNormHighlight] = { "#a7c080", "#272e33", "#272e33" }, // Bright green for matches inside normal rows
	[SchemeOut]           = { "#272e33", "#83c092", "#83c092" }, // Soft aqua for multi-completions
};
